# scripts/guards/check-no-hardcoded-column-lists.allowlist
#
# Phase 0b.2b (operator-authorized 2026-05-04) — lenient baseline.
# Each entry is a pre-existing hand-written `*_COLUMNS` / `*_COLS`
# constant in `apps/api/src/features/` that pre-dates this guard's
# landing. NEW such constants cannot be allowlisted (the lenient
# baseline is for pre-existing drift only).
#
# Format (Phase 0a.7 expiry-policy compliant):
#   <file>:<constant>  # class: A|B | <BUG-XXX> — <reason> | expires: <YYYY-MM-DD> (cascade: <BUG-XXX>)
#
# Class A (drift debt) — "all columns of a table". When a migration
# adds a column, the hand-written constant goes silently stale. Drain
# pattern: replace with `import { <TABLE>_COLUMNS } from
# '../../db/types/<table>'` (auto-generated runtime constant from
# Phase 0b.2a emitter extension).
#
# Class B (projection subset) — privacy redaction, role-based filter,
# or other intentional column-list narrowing where the omission IS the
# mechanism. The CANONICAL placement for Class B is `// @column-list-
# projection-exempt: <reason>` annotation in-source (within ±10 lines
# of the declaration), NOT this allowlist. If a Class A allowlist
# entry turns out to be Class B during 0b.2c drain, the right action
# is: (a) add the in-source annotation, AND (b) remove this allowlist
# entry. The annotation is the canonical mechanism; allowlist is for
# pre-existing drift only.
#
# 156 baseline entries seeded 2026-05-04 (150 initially + 6 newly-
# detected `export const` form added in cycle-1 absorb of L5 detection-
# scope gap finding). All pre-existing in HEAD before Phase 0b.2b's
# guard landed. Drain umbrella: BUG-PHASE-0B-2B-CASCADE-DRAIN-COLUMN-
# LISTS (S2). Drains as constants migrate to auto-generated imports
# per CLAUDE.md §15 + Phase 0b.2 plan.
#
# Stale-entry detection: the guard exits 2 if an allowlist entry no
# longer corresponds to a violation (constant migrated, file removed,
# OR in-source annotation added). Forces self-cleaning as drain
# proceeds.
#
# 2 Class B sites are NOT in this allowlist — they carry in-source
# `@column-list-projection-exempt:` annotations:
#   - apps/api/src/features/roles/receptionistFeatureRoutes.ts:
#     PHONE_TRIAGE_COLUMNS_FULL (paired projection; nurse-only)
#     PHONE_TRIAGE_COLUMNS_REDACTED (privacy redaction; receptionist)
#
# Expiry-policy: per-entry (added 2026-05-04 per Phase 0a.7 retrofit)
# Each non-comment line carries an `| expires: <YYYY-MM-DD> (cascade: <BUG>)`
# annotation. Entries past their expiry date fail the merge gate via
# `scripts/guards/check-allowlist-expiry.ts`.

apps/api/src/features/allergies/allergyRepository.ts:ALLERGY_COLUMNS  # class: A | BUG-PHASE-0B-2B-CASCADE-DRAIN-COLUMN-LISTS — pre-existing hand-written column-list (Class A drift debt — full-table projection candidate; Class B re-classification via `// @column-list-projection-exempt` annotation if intentional projection); drain in 0b.2c via auto-generated import from `apps/api/src/db/types/<table>` | expires: 2026-12-31 (cascade: BUG-PHASE-0B-2B-CASCADE-DRAIN-COLUMN-LISTS)
